wiki.summary: “Mastermind” is the closing track to Taylor Swift’s tenth studio album “Midnights“. She revealed the song’s title and track number in the first video of her TikTok game 'Midnight Mayhem With Me' on September 21, 2022. Swift reaffirms that she thinks that she and her long-time partner actor Joe Alwyn were meant for each other, but she also schemed and made up a plan to ensure that they would be together. Once she admits this to her lover, he just smiles because he already knew that something like that was in her nature. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Mastermind” is the closing track to Taylor Swift’s tenth studio album “Midnights“. She revealed the song’s title and track number in the first video of her TikTok game 'Midnight Mayhem With Me' on September 21, 2022. Swift reaffirms that she thinks that she and her long-time partner actor Joe Alwyn were meant for each other, but she also schemed and made up a plan to ensure that they would be together. Once she admits this to her lover, he just smiles because he already knew that something like that was in her nature. The title is also a nod to her fans calling Swift a “mastermind” for her careful planning of Easter eggs and releases. Taylor unveiled the “Mastermind” title in a TikTok video where she drew a random ping pong ball from a bingo machine. Since the ball had the number 13 on it, she announced the name of ” Midnights” track 13: “Mastermind”. Read more on Last.fm.
